title: Jessica Ennis-Hill: Speed Takes Goals - adidas
description:
Setting a target is the first step to reaching it. It helps Olympic champion Jessica Ennis-Hill find the an extra gear and hit the next level of performance. Having something to aim for helps her do better than before. Now she’s out to defend her title. Speed takes goals. Ennis-Hill is a creator of speed. 
-------------------------------------

Warning: This video contains flashing imagery. Viewer discretion advised.

From the pool to the hockey field. From spikes on the track to spikes on the volleyball court. From kick-off to the final whistle, adidas supports and encourages the love of sport, no matter the game. 

adidas sponsors some of the best athletes in the world including: Ajee Wilson, Tori Bowie, Shaunae Miller, Morgan Brian, Simona Halep, Garbiñe Muguruza, Ellie Simmonds, Jaqueline Carvalho, Allison Schmitt, Tyla Nathan-Wong, Eva De Goede, Jessica Ennis-Hill, Bia & Bianca, Mayra Aguiar, Rosangela Santos and Laura Trott.

transcripts: Hahaha. Setting goals is really important it raises your level of expectation on performance, but you have to have things to focus on, and things to give you that drive when you don't want to get up and train because the weather is horrible and your body is hurting. You always have that motivation of wanting to better what you've done run a little bit faster, jump a little bit higher I'm very much an explosive athlete. I have that natural speed I can just find that extra gear and push on, my ultimate goal is to get back on the podium and defend my title.
